    "caption": "Nighttime prowler with a scent gland and a love of coffee.",
    "shortDescription": "Civets are cat-like mammals from Africa and Asia with spotted coats, ringed tails, and very active scent glands — they smear a thick musky paste called civetone onto branches and rocks to mark their territory. The world's most expensive coffee is made from beans that have passed through a civet's digestive system. Fun fact: Civets are not cats at all — they're more closely related to mongooses and hyenas."
